The Sunken Sanctum

The Sunken Sanctum was the hidden proving-ground of the Spirebound Conclave,
a mountain academy in the Cinderteeth Range chartered to preserve dangerous
magical knowledge. Its founding doctrine of Continuance held that no
discovery, oath, or lesson should die with its keeper.

Three factions divided the Conclave's inner circle, each championing a
different force:

  The Ember Canon - will forged through suffering, tempered by fire.
  The Prism Thesis - memory stabilized through crystal harmonics.
  The Pale Ledger  - testimony preserved through spirit imprinting.

When border wars severed supply routes and killed the outer guard, the
Conclave reframed Continuance from scholarly ideal to survival engine.
Volunteers were sought, then expected, then quietly replaced by condemned
debtors transferred under sealed warrants from lowland magistrates. The
language of the records changed: 'binding' instead of coercion, 'elevation'
instead of vivisection, 'custody' instead of imprisonment.

Flamebound Sentinels were wounded veterans offered 'rebirth' in fire-etched
armor. Shadow Stalkers were scout prototypes whose predatory adaptation loops
could not be leashed. Spirit Mages were not true mages but mnemonic echoes
chained to duties they could no longer complete.

The catastrophe came as a cascade. An authorized change order in the conduit
matrix, countersigned by rival offices, introduced contradictory lock states
during a seismic event. Upper armouries ignited. Crystal conduits fractured
into uncontrolled growth and electrical arcing. Undercroft pumps reversed,
drawing glacial melt into ritual basements.

Regional powers declared the mountain cursed and deliberately collapsed the
upper approaches. The sanctum was not merely lost. It was entombed by policy.
No recovery team arrived. Its surviving systems still pulse in the dark,
preserving horrors that the Conclave started and never finished.
